We can do this.  Are you ready?

We need to show the world that it is possible to both support the rights of the unborn AND provide a system  where they not only survive, but thrive!
We need to recognize that all people, the elderly, the sick, the disabled, the incarcerated, the poor...they all have value...

We need real, #WholeLife policies that put people first. 
We need policies that encourage families. 
We need to encourage business models that recognize  the dignity of people and labor.  
We need to promote the #OwnershipEconomy
...
...How can we encourage policies that drive wages down while profits skyrocket?  Why does Wall Street get all the beneficial breaks and Main Street takes all the tough breaks?  Enough!...

...have increased rates of absenteeism.  Fail.  More likely to live in poverty. Fail.  Fail Fail Fail.  I'm chronically pissed off about this.  How can we encourage businesses to move jobs overseas with rotten trade agreements?...

...Politicians fund their priorities.  Our kids who go to school hungry don't learn as well.  Fail.  Our kids who go hungry tend to have reduced outcomes in life.  Fail.  More likely to be incarcerated. Fail.  Be addicted to drugs and alcohol. Fail.  Have chronic health issues...
...We are letting critical waivers that allow communities to feed their kids during record inflation and a likely food shortage.  We are failing our kids...

...I had NO idea that God lead me there because I was going to have to help my community plan to feed kids because my Government didn't find them to be a priority.  We have not updated the Child Nutrition Reauthorization in a very long time.  We are failing our kids...

...When I went back to school because I couldn't afford my student loans(yeah, it was cheaper to pay out of pocket for Community College than to pay back my student loans), I learned menu planning and meal prep as part of Restaurant Management...

...Now to hear that @SenRandPaul is going to block that, my mind is blown.  My day job is Technology Librarian.  Why did I help found @TeamVittlesOH to encourage libraries to get involved in anti-hunger programs?  Because I had to...more

Long post ahead.  I was happy to hear that Congress was coming to a rare point of agreement to give kids free meals in school.  I can't think of anything more needed as a long term investment in our nation and a short term imperative.  ...continued
